	<title>Rounding</title>

    <p>
    Nearest integer values tying away from zero are calculated using round <link xref="function">function</link>.
    </p>
    <example>
    <p>
    round (0.5)
    </p>
    </example>

    <p>
    Nearest interger values toward -∞ also known as floor values are calculated using the ⌊ and ⌋ symbols or floor <link xref="function">function</link>.
    </p>
    <example>
    <p>
    ⌊0.5⌋
    </p>
    <p>
    floor (0.5)
    </p>
    </example>

    <p>
    Nearest interger values toward +∞ also known as ceiling values are calculated using the ⌈ and ⌉ symbols or ceil <link xref="function">function</link>.
    </p>
    <example>
    <p>
    ⌈0.5⌉
    </p>
    <p>
    ceil (0.5)
    </p>
    </example>
